"'''Fair Prey'''" is a short story by [[Daniel Wallace]]. It was published in [[Star Wars Gamer 1|''Star Wars Gamer'' 1]] in [[2000]] by [[Wizards of the Coast]] as a sequel to Wallace's earlier story ''[[The Great Herdship Heist]]''. It was originally approved to run in issue [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 18|18]] of the ''[[Star Wars Adventure Journal]]'' but that issue was never published.<ref name="Interview">{{WebCite|url=http://www.myuselessknowledge.com/swfa/EG.html|text=Star Wars Fanboy Association Interview|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/DCpJt}}</ref>

==Plot summary==
When [[Cecil Noone]] tries to unload a stolen [[Hapan]] [[Gun of Command]] on the backwater planet of [[Kabal/Legends|Kabal]], he tries to strike a bargain with [[Krish (species)/Legends|Krish]] [[Hunting/Legends|hunter]] [[Tyro Viveca/Legends|Tyro Viveca]]. Tyro instead steals the [[Weapon/Legends|weapon]] and throws Cecil into his hunting grounds, where he will be stalked as game. Cecil desperately races to freedom, briefly assisted by a fellow prisoner, a vicious [[Lamproid/Legends|Florn Lamproid]], before finally escaping with the aid of his fellow [[Thief/Legends|thieves]].

==Continuity==
Background text that accompanied this short story cited the [[Wikipedia:1924|1924]] short story [[Wikipedia:The Most Dangerous Game|''The Most Dangerous Game'']] by [[Wikipedia:Richard Connell|Richard Connell's]] as inspiration. The same story inspired the [[2011]] episodes of the [[Star Wars: The Clone Wars|Clone Wars]] [[Padawan Lost]] and [[Wookiee Hunt]]. <ref name="TERC" />

